<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB05622</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT MANDATING THE RIGHT TO PROTECT ONESELF, FAMILY, PROPERTY AND OTHERS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Declares it the policy of the State to guarantee and protect the right of qualified citizens to own and possess firearms; Aims to simplify the redundant firearm application process to encourage new and existing owners to have their firearms licensed; Seeks therefore to merge the License to Own and Possess Firearms (LTOPF) and Permit to Carry Firearm Outside of Residence (PTCFOR) into a single license (LTOPF); Defines several terms among others as “concealed carry” and “open carry”.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>TEVES, ARNOLFO JR. A.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2017-05-11</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON PUBLIC ORDER AND SAFETY ON 2017-05-17</td></tr></table>